/*
  jkimyei.inference.expected_value.mdn.bnf
  =================================================
  Fresh authored surface for MDN ExpectedValue training orchestration.

  <training-file> ::= "TRAINING" "{" <kv-list> "}"
  <kv-list>       ::= (<key> "=" <value> ";")*

  Required keys:
    VERSION = jkimyei.inference.expected_value.mdn.v1
    TRAINING_ID
    TASK = mdn_expected_value_inference
    COMPONENT_ID
    LEARNING_RATE
    BATCH_SIZE

  Optional keys:
    OPTIMIZER = adam
    MAX_STEPS = integer >= 0
    GRAD_CLIP_NORM = float >= 0
    CHECKPOINT_EVERY = integer >= 0, checkpoint every N optimizer steps
                       to the launcher checkpoint path, replacing the previous
                       checkpoint at that path
    REPORT_EVERY = integer > 0, rewrite the report every N attempted steps;
                   a final report is written when the last cadence write is
                   not already current
    VALIDATION_EVERY = 0
    SEED = integer >= 0, seeds CPU and CUDA generators when applicable
    FREEZE_REPRESENTATION = true | false

  V1 MDN training requires FREEZE_REPRESENTATION=true. Joint training is
  deliberately outside this surface. Validation cadence is not implemented in
  v1, so nonzero VALIDATION_EVERY is rejected instead of being ignored. CUDA
  seeding does not imply fully deterministic CUDA kernels in v1.
*/
